flowRoot.flowPara: View the current blog post (make sure you save changes first)
Screen options for the current admin page. Always check this for cool hidden features.
Click this to access the home page of your website from any backend page.
Dashboard home page. View summary of your website, see updates and access quick actions.
Logout of WordPress or access your profile
Click this button to save any changes and make them live on your website.
Place a blog post into categories so it's easier for your customers to browse them.
This is where you can enter a custom Excerpt for a blog post. Ensure "Excerpt" is enabled in Screen Options above.
Change themes, widgets, background, logo, font and more.
Choose where the sidebar should display on this page (or the default for this page type).
You can tag your blog posts with keywords as well if you want.
Blog posts live here. New blog posts will appear in date order on your website.
Automatic theme updates can be enabled from here.
All your shop settings, products and orders are in these two menu items. WooCommerce is great!
Quick access to create new Pages, Posts, Products and more..
Media is all your images. Upload images in here, or you can upload them while edting individual blog/post/product pages.
Pages are here. Home page, Contact Page, Our Gallery, things like that. These are different to blog posts.
New blog post comments will appear here. You can disable comments from Settings > Discussion.
Contact form settings are here. e.g. Contact Us page and the Footer Signup.
Add plugins to your website to extend the default functionality.
If you make a mistake you can always swap back to an older revision here.
Change the current Page Title style. Site default can be set in Customizer.
Change the current Page Width. Default can be set in Customizer. Disable sidebar for best full width layout.
Change the current Page border style. Default can be set in Customizer.
Go to Appearance > Widgets to choose which widgets should display in this widget area.
Set a featured blog post image here. Try to keep images about 1500px wide and under 1MB. Uploading straight from your camera can slow down the website.
Change the current image style (or shown/hidden status). Default can be set in Customizer.
